Despite maximal medical therapy, she develops respiratory arrest and dies.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the classification of this death?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Indirect maternal death","Direct maternal death","Antenatal maternal death","Pregnancy-associated death","Late maternal death"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient died from severe asthma during pregnancy. \u003Cstrong\u003EIndirect maternal death\u003C/strong\u003E is the correct classification as it refers to deaths from pre-existing medical conditions or conditions that develop during pregnancy that are not directly related to pregnancy but are aggravated by the physiological changes of pregnancy. The normal respiratory changes of pregnancy (increased minute ventilation, reduced functional residual capacity) can worsen asthma control.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Edirect maternal death\u003C/strong\u003E would be one resulting from obstetric complications such as pre-eclampsia, postpartum haemorrhage, or amniotic fluid embolism. This patient\u0027s death was not due to an obstetric complication.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAntenatal maternal death\u003C/strong\u003E simply describes the timing of death (during pregnancy) rather than the cause, and therefore does not appropriately classify the underlying reason for death.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Epregnancy-associated death\u003C/strong\u003E includes any death while pregnant or within 42 days postpartum, regardless of cause. While this death would be included in pregnancy-associated mortality statistics, this classification is too broad and does not capture the relationship between the medical condition and pregnancy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELate maternal death\u003C/strong\u003E refers to deaths occurring between 42 days and one year after the end of pregnancy. This death occurred during pregnancy and therefore cannot be classified as a late maternal death.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Indirect maternal deaths occur from pre-existing conditions or conditions that develop during pregnancy but are not directly due to obstetric causes.","Direct maternal deaths result from obstetric complications of pregnancy."],"references":["Australian Institute of Health and Welfare. Australia\u2019s mothers and babies 2021: in brief. Canberra: AIHW; 2023 [cited 2024 Nov 5]. Available from: https://www.aihw.gov.au/getmedia/7dc17a03-6004-4f84-8466-122ea540af90/aihw-per-121.pdf"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44630"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14894"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"44630","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/44630"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-05T17:37:16+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-05T17:38:33+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7585"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"59219"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"23","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/23"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd30","name":"Obstetrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Diagnosis","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":nul